<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Corish-MT on 04-10-2002 02:19 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Hmmm, a few more things (you've got me thinking)...

Not sure if this is possible in your mid-20s, but ideally, a single-mob fight should only take 20% of your mana pool (maybe 30%).  I've found this to be true starting somewhere in my mid-30s, while the druids and wizards are constantly saying 20m, 30m after a fight, I'm saying 80m and the puller runs off and pulls another one.  My reason for saying a fight should leave you at 80% (which you can usually med back up before the next fight)?  60-70% of your mana bar is for emergency use only (picture 4 mobs suddenly showing up at camp, you're going to burn a lot of mana on crowd-control, healing people who got aggro until things get locked down and you can start medding again).  All of a sudden, you'll be looked at as "smart" for saving your mana for an emergency rather than nuking to speed up fights.

Maybe not possible in the late 20s, unless you have a solid main tank, and people are keeping aggro on the tank and not ping-ponging the mob.  It was just something that I thought of as I wondered if, since I was always at 80m, if I should start nuking.

-------

I also wanted to revisit my numbers on whether more HP means less efficient healing...

1000 HP tank
500 dmg per fight from a mob
1 minute per mob fight
I regain 25% of my mana each minute
I can heal 2000 HP if I'm at full mana.

In that scenario, I will never run out of mana because I med back 500 HP worth of healing power each minute (25% of 2000 HP) which I then heal the tank with because they took 500 HP worth of damage during that minute.

However, if the mobs suddenly start dealing 600 dmg per fight, and the pull rate is still once per minute.  I'm going to run out of mana after about 20 fights (I start with 2000 HP of healing power, but only have 1900 HP of healing power after the first minute because healing the melee took 30% of my mana, and I only med back 25% of my mana pool per minute, meaning that I'm losing 5% mana per minute fought).

Once I run dry (around 20 minutes), we have to stop and meditate for 4 minutes for me to med back to full.  And the only reason is that the mobs did more damage per minute then my meditating could keep up with.

------------------
Corish, 46 Cleric of Morell-Thule</TEXTAREA>
